SCENARIO-02 – Laptop Will Not Power On

Business Context
A Horizon Freight Logistics sales representative reported their corporate laptop would not power on before a scheduled client meeting, risking missed communications and delayed order processing.

Ticket Summary
Ticket ID: HD-0002
Category: Hardware Issue
Impact: Single User
Urgency: High
Priority: P1
Device: Lenovo ThinkPad X1 Carbon (Windows 11)

User Reported Issue
“My laptop won’t turn on. No lights or display activity when pressing the power button.”
CompTIA A+ Troubleshooting Methodology

1️⃣ Identify the Problem
Laptop does not power on.
No fan noise.
No LED indicators.
User reports device was working previous day.

2️⃣ Establish Theory
Possible causes considered:
Drained battery
Faulty power adapter
Loose charging cable
Failed battery
Motherboard failure

Most likely cause:
Battery fully discharged and not charging due to loose power connection.

3️⃣ Test the Theory
Verified outlet functionality using alternate device.
Tested with known-good power adapter.
Observed charging LED indicator activate.
Attempted power-on after 5 minutes of charge.
Device powered on successfully.

Theory confirmed: Power delivery issue due to faulty adapter.

4️⃣ Plan of Action
Replace defective power adapter.
Verify battery health in BIOS diagnostics.
Educate user on cable strain prevention.

5️⃣ Verify Functionality
System booted successfully.
Battery charging confirmed.
No BIOS errors detected.
User confirmed access to email and CRM system.

6️⃣ Document Findings

Root Cause:
Faulty power adapter preventing battery charge.

Resolution:
Replaced adapter and verified system functionality.

Preventative Action:
Issued new OEM charger and advised proper cable handling.

Time to Resolve: 22 minutes

Business Impact
Sales operations restored prior to scheduled client engagement.

Skills Demonstrated:
Hardware diagnostics
Power troubleshooting
Adapter validation
BIOS verification
Preventative hardware guidance
Structured A+ troubleshooting methodology
